license: MIT
year: 2026
keywords:
  - audio deepfake detection
  - source separation
  - self-supervised learning
  - wav2vec2
  - ESDD2
  - CompSpoofV2
  - BiLSTM
  - attention
abstract: >
  DPADD-ES is a component-aware audio deepfake detection system submitted to the
  ESDD2 ICME 2026 Grand Challenge. It explicitly disentangles speech and
  environmental latent representations via mask-based separation with a Frobenius
  orthogonality loss, achieving validation macro-F1 of 0.8923 on CompSpoofV2.
